{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3351066,"name":"","username":"Farquaad","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/farquaad/{size}/218709_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-03T02:07:55.378Z","cooked":"<p>My team recently got a <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> CANdle that we intend to use for LEDs. We followed the provided documentation and it did not work as intended. Currently the CANdles built in LEDs display red, white, and pink of three of the LEDs, and the LED strip itself is a plethora of colors in an irregular pattern. By this I mean that half of the LEDs are off and the others are random colors. We are rather stumped because we followed the documentation and encountered errors. Any help would be greatly appreciated.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-04-03T02:07:55.378Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":624,"reads":187,"readers_count":186,"score":3162.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":461134,"topic_slug":"candle-with-leds-not-working","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63302,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/candle-with-leds-not-working/461134/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3351082,"name":"Cole Wilson","username":"colew","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-03T02:23:34.038Z","cooked":"<p>Hello! Not sure if this will help but have you tried changing the LED strip type in your code? There are many different options like WRGB GBR etc. You can try setting it with <code>candle.configLEDType(LEDStripType.*);</code> If you are seeing “random” colors that might mean your code is sending out 4 bytes of data (WRGB) rather than 3 (RGB) or something like that.</p>
<p>Also, have you confirmed that you have the correct number of LEDs chosen if you are using any animations?</p>
<p>Finally, it’s also worth checking that any metal contacts on the back of external LED strips aren’t shorted. My team bought some LED lights for the CANdle and we accidentally shorted out a small section by sticking them on metal, causing “random” colors to appear further down the strip.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-04-03T02:23:34.038Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":180,"readers_count":179,"score":56.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":461134,"topic_slug":"candle-with-leds-not-working","display_username":"Cole Wilson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62619,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/candle-with-leds-not-working/461134/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3351114,"name":"","username":"Farquaad","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/farquaad/{size}/218709_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-03T02:39:24.179Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you for the response! We are using <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> Addressable LEDs that are GRB. We have them set to GRB in the code as well as in the config for the CANdle on Phoenix Tuner X.</p>
<p>I have currently not run any animations through, just solid colors. But I do not know how many segments are on the LED, which is definitely an issue. Is the segment count just how any LEDs are on the strip?</p>
<p>I will definitely make sure the first thing I do next meeting is check for shorts. It would really suck if this were the case because we just received them from <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> yesterday, and today was the first time they have been used. I will look for shorts then check all the code, then ill test other LEDs.</p>
<p>Again thank you for the response, its very helpful to see all the ways we can trouble shoot this.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-04-03T02:39:24.179Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":147,"readers_count":146,"score":49.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":461134,"topic_slug":"candle-with-leds-not-working","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":62619,"username":"colew","name":"Cole Wilson","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/f19dbf/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63302,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/candle-with-leds-not-working/461134/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3351141,"name":"Cole Wilson","username":"colew","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-03T03:18:06.315Z","cooked":"<p>The segment count for the animations should be the number of LEDs on the strip + the 8 CANdle built-in LEDs I believe (the device treats external strips as an extension of the 8 onboard LEDs). Happy to help! I hope your team can get them working.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-04-03T03:18:06.315Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":121,"readers_count":12