<p>We bought some <span class="abbreviation">CTRE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Cross The Road Electronics"></template></span> LEDs but bought a larger quantity of some from Amazon. They don’t look like it but are very fragile and we got breakage turning corners of the robot structure. We fixed the breaks and tested and had another break to fix.</p>
<p>If the CANdle isn’t working right with no LEDs plugged into it (except its internal ones) then that sounds like you are trying to use a 5 volt supply instead of the 12 v supply to the CANdle.</p>
<p>Consider possible <span class="abbreviation">CAN<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Controller Area Network"></template></span> wiring trouble.</p>
<p>Needing an extra power supply on the LEDs and then overheating sounds like a break in the string and then using the wrong voltage boost to bypass the break or reverse polarity wiring errors.</p>
<p>Arrow on LEDs goes away from the CANdle as already mentioned.</p>
<p>The CANdle is rated for 6 A 5V output and our LED string was significantly less than that but the CANdle quit working. The next day it recovered but clearly the one we got can’t handle even 5 A on the 5 V output.</p>
<p>Make sure your LEDs are plugged into the right voltage. All of my team’s are 5V but I see 12V strings are available.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-04-03T22:50:11.064Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":70,"readers_count":69,"score":54.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":461134,"topic_slug":"candle-with-leds-not-working","display_username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":63302,"username":"Farquaad","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/farquaad/{size}/218709_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24594,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/candle-with-leds-not-working/461134/8","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3352060,"name":"","username":"Farquaad","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/farquaad/{size}/218709_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-04T01:44:31.799Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="SLAB-Mr.Thomas" data-post="8" data-topic="461134">
